# Git commits (English only)

- Write **all commit messages in English** (subject line and body).
- Use conventional style when it fits the repo, e.g. `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `docs:`.
- Do **not** use German (or other languages) in commit messages unless quoting user-facing copy.

Examples:

- `feat(cv-section): merge CV i18n into main locale files`
- `fix: correct header link contrast on document pages`
